<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id122ecb30-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1721"><num value="1721">§ 1721.</num><heading> Exchange of documents by heads of departments</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Heads of departments may exchange surplus documents for other documents and books required by them, when it is to the advantage of the public service.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id122ecb31-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1282">82 Stat. 1282</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id122ecb32-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id122ecb33-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 93 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s95">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 95</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/623">28 Stat. 623</ref>).</p>
</note>
